&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Acumen Academy&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Acumen Academy is the world’s school for social change. We aim to unleash a new generation of social innovators and leaders with the character and competence to build a more just, inclusive and sustainable world. Anyone with an internet connection, anywhere in the world, can access the practical tools, practices, resources and supportive community they need to achieve positive social change. With 1,000 Fellows and Accelerator alumni, and 1.2M&amp;nbsp; course sign-ups from 193 countries, the Acumen Academy community represents a new generation of social innovators and leaders committed to doing what’s right in a world that loves easy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Acumen Latin America&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Acumen Latin America (ALA) started operations in 2013 and has a team based in Bogotá focusing on Colombia and Perú. To date, ALA has made 19 investments totaling $11.2 million in agribusiness companies that seek to impact the livelihood of smallholder farmers principally in Colombia. Other sectors of interest are education and energy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In 2018, ALA launched the Acumen Fellows program in Colombia.&amp;nbsp; Since then, we have also adapted our online content to the context, language and channels best suited for the Latin American audience, through WhatsApp Courses.&amp;nbsp; Finally, we launched a Regional Leadership Program for rural and grassroots leaders.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Click&lt;a href=&quot;https://acumen.org/latin-america/&quot;&gt; here&lt;/a&gt; for more information on Acumen’s work in Latin America.&lt;/p&gt;
